  • Type Parameters:
    T - The object type stored in the collection.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CollectionReorderable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>, java.util.RandomAccess, javax.swing.table.TableModel

    public abstract class ArrayListWithTableModel<T>
extends ArrayListReorderable<T>
implements javax.swing.table.TableModel
    This abstract class extends the capability of an ArrayList by adding record reordering functionality and providing the skeleton implementation of a TableModel. This class fulfills the collection requirements for com.gmail.at.kevinburnseit.collections.RxTableWithMovableRecordControls. Derived classes must provide the implementation-specific details for the TableModel.
    Author:
    Kevin J. Burns

      • requestTableUpdate

        public void requestTableUpdate(int index)
        This function should be called when a list element is modified externally; that is to say:
        1. An existing item is fetched from the list using ArrayList.get(int)
        2. The item is modified by calling functions or setting member variables on that item
        3. The item's changed state needs to be updated in a table
        Calling this function requests the table to update its view of the item.
        Parameters:
        index - Index of the item to be updated
